<aura:documentation>
	<aura:description>
		<p>
			A <code>ui:outputText</code> component represents text output that is wrapped in an HTML <code>span</code> tag.
            We recommend using <code>lightning:formattedText</code> instead of <code>ui:outputText</code>.
        </p>
		<p>
        	<code>ui:outputText</code> can be used with <code>ui:inputText</code>, which takes in a text input. 
            To apply Lightning Design System styling, we recommend that you use <code>lightning:input</code> instead of <code>ui:inputText</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
			To display text, you can use an attribute value and bind it to the <code>ui:outputText</code> component.
		</p>
		<pre>&lt;aura:attribute name="myText" type="String" default="some string"/>
&lt;ui:outputText value="{!v.myText}" /></pre>
		<p>The previous example renders the following HTML.</p>
		<pre>&lt;span dir="ltr" class="uiOutputText">
    some string
&lt;/span></pre>
		
	</aura:description>	
		<aura:example name="text" ref="uiExamples:text" label="Using the ui:outputText Component">
    	<p>This example shows how you can bind data from an <code>ui:inputText</code> component.
           To apply Lightning Design System styling, we recommend that you use <code>lightning:input</code> instead of <code>ui:inputText</code>.
        </p>
        
	</aura:example>
	
</aura:documentation>
